definition: a row/a line/to set in order/to arrange/to line up/to eliminate/to drain/to push open/platoon/raft/classifier for lines, rows etc

sentences.chinese: 这些人排成一列排队一声不吭地出发了。

sentences.english: This section explains how the queueing system distributes any remaining bandwidth.
sentences.chinese: 这节解释了排队系统如何分配任何剩余带宽。

sentences.english: The farmers are queuing in the Postal Savings Bank of China.
sentences.chinese: 农民们正在中国邮政储蓄银行排队。

sentences.english: It is improper to cut in on a queue.
sentences.chinese: 突然插到排队的行列中去是不恰当的。

sentences.english: The total inability to queue and just being generally gormless beyond belief.
sentences.chinese: 没有排队的习惯，而且是难以置信的愚蠢。

sentences.english: They queued patiently to get into the auditorium.
sentences.chinese: 他们耐心地排队进入礼堂。

sentences.english: Off of one room, there is a bathroom-sized space that people are lining up to see.
sentences.chinese: 人们正排队等著参观其中一个只有厕所大小的房间。

sentences.english: Waiting in line for a chance at the operating table.
sentences.chinese: 排队等待着上手术台的机会。

sentences.english: Firstly, an M/G/1 retrial queue with two-phase service, feedback and preemptive resume discipline is considered.

sentences.english: Firstly, an M/G/1 retrial queue with two-phase service, feedback and preemptive resume discipline is considered.

sentences.english: The football fans lined up for the tickets.
Every time I go to pay calls always line up, never less than automatic payment machine.
sentences.chinese: 每次去交话费总是排队，从来不到自动交款机。

sentences.english: Uncle and I are standing in line at the hamburger kiosk.
sentences.chinese: 我和叔叔排队站在汉堡包摊前。
当有人排队加塞时我恼火。

sentences.english: The main theme of this paper is queue model with batch arrival and multi-server.
sentences.chinese: 本文主要研究批量到达的多服务台排队模型。

sentences.english: They queued to get into the cinema.
sentences.chinese: 他们排队等候进入电影院。
